# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES — REQUIRED FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT AND PRODUCTION
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. SUPABASE (REQUIRED)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Get these from your Supabase project dashboard:
# https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/YOUR_PROJECT_ID/settings/api

# Your Supabase project URL (e.g. https://abcdefg.supabase.co)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co

# Your Supabase anonymous/public key (safe to expose in client code)
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 2. EMAIL NOTIFICATIONS (SERVER-SIDE SUPABASE SECRETS)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Notifications are stored in the DB (always) AND emailed via Resend.
# Sign up free at https://resend.com — 3,000 emails/month on the free tier.
#
# Set these as Supabase Edge Function secrets (NOT in .env):
#   supabase secrets set RESEND_API_KEY="re_..."
#   supabase secrets set FROM_EMAIL="StayTrue <noreply@yourdomain.com>"
#   supabase secrets set APP_URL="https://yourdomain.com"
#
# Then deploy the edge function:
#   supabase functions deploy send-email

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 3. SUPABASE EDGE FUNCTIONS (SERVER-SIDE ONLY — auto-injected)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# These are automatically injected by Supabase into Edge Functions.
# Only set these manually if testing locally with the Supabase CLI.

# Service role key (NEVER expose this in client code)
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# QUICK START GUIDE
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. Create a Supabase project at https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Copy .env.example to .env
# 3. Fill in VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY from your dashboard
# 4. Run the SQL schema files in Supabase SQL Editor (see README.md)
# 5. (Optional) Set up Resend for email notifications
# 6. Start the dev server: npm run dev
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
